article.headline: Idaho State 85, Sacramento State 62
article.story: Idaho St 85, Sacramento St 62 POCATELLO, Idaho (AP) -- David Schroeder scored 23 points and grabbed seven rebounds as Idaho State snapped a four-game losing streak with a 85-62 win over Sacramento State Saturday night. Sacramento State (8-15, 3-7 Big Sky) controlled the game early, grabbing a quick 7-2 lead. But Idaho State (11-12, 6-4 Big Sky) took over with an 18-2 run during seven minutes midway through the first half to open up a 32-17 lead. Schroeder led the charge, hitting four three-pointers over that span. Sacramento State outscored Idaho State 11-4 over the last five minutes of the half to close the Idaho State lead to 36-28 at halftime. Sacramento State shot just 35 percent from the field in the half, including 2-17 from the three-point range. Idaho State scored the first seven points of the second half to regain a 15-point edge at 43-28. A three-pointer from Matt Stucki extended the ISU lead to 20, at 65-45, with just over 10 minutes left. Sacramento State pulled to within 13 with seven minutes to play, but Idaho State pulled away from there and cruised to victory. Idaho State shot better than 61 percent from the field for the game, and nearly 70 percent in the second half. Logan Kinghorn added 19 points and seven rebounds for Idaho State. Kris Groce led Sacramento State with 15 points.
